This should had been fixed already, swagger-tools/issues/61.  The difference between the scenario fixed and the one that is broken is that your items configuration doesn't seem to be proper, although I wonder why the structural validation isn't failing.  Long story short, here is how you are doing arrays:
js
{
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "SomeName": {
      "$ref": "SomeRef"
    }
  }
}
But based on the schema, it should be done like this:
js
{
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "$ref" "SomeRef"
   }
}
Now, swagger-tools supports the later form and that support was from the Swagger 2.0 schema.  The reason this isn't throwing a structural error is because #/definitions/schema doesn't have "additionalProperties": false anywhere in its schema.  I will mention @webron to get his opinion because I could be wrong but in the event I'm right, here is the updated version using the supported form:
