. I've updated swagger-tools/issues/#72 to describe this as I understand it.  Just know, /{type}{id} will never be supported as there is no way to tell where type ends and id begins.  Some might argue that this is one argument and its up to the implementor to take the typeWithId and parse it themselves but I will do what I can to support this in the ways possible.
. I'm expecting to have Swagger Tools supporting references properly within the next few days.  Supporting references has resulted in a near full rewrite in the library.  I'll update you when I'm done.
. While this is valid, I'm sure it's not what was intended by the user.  items can be an object or an array: https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-spec/blob/master/schemas/v2.0/schema.json#L951
. I did not, I've not put any time to swagger-tools due to other projects.  I'll get it fixed tomorrow.
. int16 is not a valid format.  See the Data Types section of the Swagger 2.0 specification.
. But int16 is not a valid JSON Schema format either.  So any JSON Schema validator will bomb on this without registering a custom validator.
. In fact, I just tested this here https://json-schema-validator.herokuapp.com/ with the following: 
js
{
  "type": "number",
  "format": "int16"
}
And got when validating the schema:
[ {
  "level" : "warning",
  "schema" : {
    "loadingURI" : "#",
    "pointer" : ""
  },
  "domain" : "validation",
  "keyword" : "format",
  "message" : "format attribute \"int16\" not supported",
  "attribute" : "int16"
} ]
However, using a valid (JSON Schema format or Swagger format) format works just fine.  Here is an example:
js
{
  "type": "string",
  "format": "email"
}
. Of course, most JSON Schema validators have ways to register custom validators...which is how the sway validator used by swagger-editor handle's Swagger's formats.  But registering custom, non-Swagger and non-JSON Schema validators, seemed to be outside the scope of things so nothing was ever supported in swagger-tools or sway.
. I've deleted my comments.  I made a few of them not realizing the implementation linked to was giving a warning and not an error.  Anyway, the JSON Schema validator swagger-editor uses is z-schema and I'm filing a bug there to allow us to not fail on unknown format.
