itainteasy:
OK so here is how to reproduce the error when you are trying to bring your json into the swagger online editor: 
1. While you're at http://editor.swagger.io/ we goto File -> Paste JSON...
2. Paste the following JSON (_it was generated by using File -> Open Example... and choosing minimal):  {
   "swagger": "2.0",
   "info": {
     "version": "0.0.0",
     "title": "Simple API"
   },
   "paths": {
     "/": {
       "get": {
         "responses": {
           "200": {
             "description": "OK"
           }
         }
       }
     }
   }
   }
3. You will get the error:

message: "options.definition is required"
code: "ERROR_THROWN_BY_SWAY_CODE:undefined"
4. Now, let's add a root property called "definition" and encapsulate everything (above) to become it's property: {
   "definition": {
     "swagger": "2.0",
     "info": {
       "version": "0.0.0",
       "title": "Simple API"
     },
     "paths": {
       "/": {
         "get": {
           "responses": {
             "200": {
               "description": "OK"
             }
           }
         }
       }
     }
   }
   }
   You will now get "✔ Valid Swagger".. click Import.
5. Now the editor is displaying an error:
Unknown Error
Unable to identify the Swagger version or the Swagger version is unsupported
This is because we had to add the definition property to the root and move everything into it to pass the paste & import step.
Simply delete the first line of which has definition: and viola.

*Your final YAML looks like:*
yaml
swagger: '2.0'
info:
  version: 0.0.0
  title: Simple API
paths:
  /:
    get:
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
If you use the editor to File -> Download JSON you will have to do this again to get things back into it. Per the Swagger 2.0 Spec the field/property "definition" is not allowed anywhere.
I recommend using https://restunited.com/ against your exports from https://www.getpostman.com/ to handle proper conversions for now at least it's the simplest/quickest way to convert your postman collections into swagger &/or YAML.
I'd put my money on this being strictly related to the editor itself expecting this field.. I'll check out the code when I get some more free time.
Hope this helps!
