MichaelRSilva:
Yukonn. Did you solved the problem? I have a same problem.
. Hi Yukonn,
i solved it.
In the my case, i am doing the back-end with nodeJS, and the problem was with CORS, i enabled the cors.
To enable the CORS in nodeJS you can add the below code, before of the routes.
```
    var app = express();
app.use(function(req, res, next) {

    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');

    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, PUT, UPDATE, DELETE, OPTIONS');

    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Origin, X-Requested-With, Content-Type, Accept, Authorization');

    next();

});

```
