Revert to use resolved spec for codegen - this is the simplest option but means going back to the InlineResponse200 problem
Option 1, plus rework resolver in swagger-js to address the InlineResponse200 problem (not sure if this is possible as it will be a breaking change in terms of the resolved output)
Option 1, plus modify codegen to take the $$ref field as hint for model name when generating code
Implement new codegen-friendly resolver to be used by editor when generating code

